      • sort

        static <T> Object sort(Object array,
                       Comparator<T> comparator,
                       Arrays.Sorter.CompareMethod method,
                       boolean descending)
        Sorts an array in ascending order using a certain method.
        Type Parameters:
        T - - the component type of the array.
        Parameters:
        array - - the array to sort.
        comparator - - the comparator to use if the method is to sort the elements based on a comparator; otherwise ignored
        method - - the method to sort the array by;
        • 0 - Comparable casting
        • 1 - Hash Code comparisons
        • 2 - Comparator invocation
        descending - - whether or not this array is sorted in ascending (false) or descending order (true)
        Returns:
        null if the method given was not supported or did not exist; otherwise the sorted array in ascending order.

      • sort0

        private static <T> Object sort0(Object array,
                                Object newArray,
                                Arrays.Sorter.CompareMethod method,
                                Comparator<T> comparator,
                                boolean descending)
        Sorts an array into ascending order using recursion and selection sort utilizing the Comparable interface.
        Type Parameters:
        T - - the component type of the array.
        Parameters:
        array - - the array to sort (only used for cloning on this method's first stack, afterwards overridden to represent some element in the cloned array).
        newArray - - the cloned array that will be sorted; must be null for proper sorting
        method - - the method used to compare the elements; only used in findKey(Object, CompareMethod, Comparator, boolean)
        comparator - - the comparator used if the method is to compare the elements using a Comparator instance; ignored otherwise.
        descending - - whether the array is being sorted in descending order or not.
        Returns:
        the sorted array.

      • findKey

        private static <T> void findKey(Object array,
                                Arrays.Sorter.CompareMethod method,
                                Comparator<T> comparator,
                                boolean descending)
        Finds the minimum or maximum value in an array after the indices specified by sortTrace depending on whether the array is being sorted in ascending or descending order.
        Type Parameters:
        T - - the component type of the array.
        Parameters:
        array - - the array to look through.
        method - - the method used to compare the elements.
        comparator - - the comparator used if the method compares the elements using a comparator instance.
        descending - - whether the array is being sorted in descending order or not.
